WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.400
Hi everyone, I'm Ko Ju-Chun.

00:00:03.080 --> 00:00:07.680
Today I want to share a tool that really impressed me.

00:00:08.440 --> 00:00:10.760
It's called oMLX.

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:13.060
If you have a Mac

00:00:13.320 --> 00:00:15.360
and want to run AI models locally,

00:00:16.120 --> 00:00:19.459
you've probably used LM Studio or Ollama.

00:00:19.719 --> 00:00:21.240
But you must have hit the same problem —

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:23.559
it's incredibly slow.

00:00:23.799 --> 00:00:26.120
A single question takes minutes to answer.

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:27.400
oMLX

00:00:27.639 --> 00:00:29.700
completely solves this problem.

00:00:30.200 --> 00:00:32.520
It's designed specifically for Apple Silicon,

00:00:33.279 --> 00:00:36.619
leveraging MLX's unified memory architecture,

00:00:37.639 --> 00:00:40.959
plus tiered KV caching and paged attention,

00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:44.040
boosting inference speed by over 10x.

00:00:44.799 --> 00:00:46.080
The best part?

00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:48.900
It supports multi-agent concurrency.

00:00:49.400 --> 00:00:52.740
You can run multiple OpenClaw lobsters simultaneously,

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.560
sharing the same prefix cache.

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:59.400
Even a base Mac Mini with 16GB works.

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:01.959
Installation is super easy.

00:01:02.200 --> 00:01:04.760
Download the DMG and drag to install,

00:01:05.519 --> 00:01:07.839
or use Homebrew with one command.

00:01:08.360 --> 00:01:10.139
Completely free and open source.

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:15.260
I've prepared a complete step-by-step tutorial on CanFly.ai,

00:01:16.040 --> 00:01:18.839
from installation to connecting OpenClaw —

00:01:19.099 --> 00:01:20.379
done in 10 minutes.

00:01:21.400 --> 00:01:22.680
Give it a try!
